Importing Libraries¶

In [1]:
import cv2
from PIL import Image 
from IPython.display import display 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

Loading and Displaying the Original Image¶

In [10]:
image = cv2.imread("PicsArt_02-28-09.06.27.jpg")
display(Image.fromarray(image))

Converting Image to RGB Format¶

In [11]:
image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
display(Image.fromarray(image))

Converting Image to Grayscale¶

In [12]:
grayscale_image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
display(Image.fromarray(grayscale_image))

Inverting the Grayscale Image¶

In [13]:
inverted_gray_image = 255 - grayscale_image
display(Image.fromarray(inverted_gray_image))

Applying Gaussian Blur¶

In [14]:
blurred_image = cv2.GaussianBlur(inverted_gray_image,(35,35),0)
display(Image.fromarray(blurred_image))

Inverting the Blurred Image¶

In [15]:
inverted_blur_image = 255 - blurred_image 
display(Image.fromarray(inverted_blur_image))

Creating, Saving and Displaying the Pencil Sketch¶

In [16]:
pencil_sketch = cv2.divide(grayscale_image, inverted_blur_image, scale = 256.0)
In [17]:
cv2.imwrite("Final_pencil_sketch.png",pencil_sketch)
display(Image.fromarray(pencil_sketch))
